@Node "Setup" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - Setup"

  @{u}@{b}Setup@{ub}@{uu}


    First of all you must set MUI_BW.MiamiPanel as default panel:
    Go to "MiamiDX/Gui/Control panel settings.../Panel module"
    and select "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel".

    An interface will appear in the panel iff it is set to do
    that. In order to make an interface to be in the panel,
    go to "MiamiDx/Interfaces", doubleclick the interface and
    select the checkmark "Control panel".

    Some settings of the panel are available in
    "MiamiDx/GUI/Control panel settings..".
    There you may set:
    - Hotkey
    - Refresh time
    - Show on startup
    - Show transfer rate
    - Show total traffic
    - Show control gadgets
    - Show speed
    - Show online time
    - Show onl/off gadgets

    There are ignored:
    - Font (set it in MUI)
    - Public screen (set it in MUI)

    Other settings you should take care of are the MUI ones:

    - Windows/Fonts/Small for the On/Offline buttons

    - Groups/Frame/Normal for the Miami gadgets group frame
    - Groups/Bacground/Framed for the Miami gadgets group background

    - NListviews/Misc/Misc2/Leading to something like 6 or 8
    - NListviews/ScrollBar/Horiz_Scrollbar to FullAuto
    - NListviews/ScrollBar/Vertical_Scrollbar to FullAuto

    The MUI_BW.MiamiPanel GUI is described @{"here" Link "GUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "GUI" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - GUI"

  @{u}@{b}GUI@{ub}@{uu}


    MUI_BW.MiamiPanel opens a very simple interface,
    whose main elements are:

    - @{"Menus             " Link "Menus"}
    - @{"Interface list    " Link "IFList"}
    - @{"Miami ctrls group " Link "CGroup"}
    - About window

    The main window is based upon BWin.mcc, so it is a
    borderless and custom window. It may be controlled
    via a context menu.

    ------------------------------------------------------
    Note that pressing the Help button in one of the above
    will open this guide.

@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - Menus"

  @{u}@{b}Menus@{ub}@{uu}


    The MUI_BW.MiamiPanel menus are:

    - Project

      o About
        Opens the About window

      o About MUI
        Opens the About MUI window

      o Hide
        The action taken depends on your On iconify setting:
        If you choosed Quit, the panel is quit
        If you choosed Iconify, the panel is iconified

      o Quit
        Quit the panel


    - Miami (See @{"Miami ctrls group" Link "CGroup"})

      o Show
        Open Miami GUI

      o Hide
        Iconify Miami GUI

      o Quit
        Quit Miami


    - Preferences

      o Traffic format
        - Long
          The traffic is shown in bytes
        - Short
          The traffic is shown in Kb/Mb
        - Group
          If selected the traffic is grouped

      o Rate format
        - Long
          The Rate is shown in bytes
        - Short
          The Rate is shown in Kb/Mb
        - Group
          If selected the Rate is grouped

      o Bold title
        If selected the title of the interface list is
        bold

      o Double click
        If selected, you may doubleclik on an interface
        to switch its state

      o Use sort strings
        If selected, short strings wil be uses (for
        On/Offline gadgets and State)

      o Miami ctrls
        - Top
          Put the miami ctrls group at the top
        - Bottom
          Put the miami ctrls group at the bottom
        - Left
          Put the miami ctrls group at the left
        - Right
          Put the miami ctrls group at the right
        - Framed
          If selected the Miami ctrls group is framed

      o On iconify
        This may sound strange, but because of a MiamiPanel
        as no iconified state, you may decide to simply quit
        the panel when iconified, or to really iconify it.
        If iconified with an icon, the panel searches for
        ENVARC:Sys/MiamiPanel.info .

      o Save
        Save layout (including the interfaces list width
        and order and main window position/dimensions)
        to ENVARC:

      o Use
        Save layout (including the interfaces list width
        and order) to ENV:

      o Restore
        Load the layout (including the interfaces list width
        and order) from ENV:

      o Last saved
        Load the layout (including the interfaces list width
        and order) from ENVARC:

      o MUI
        Open MUI config window

@EndNode

@Node "IFList" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - Interfaces list"

  @{u}@{b}Interfaces list@{ub}@{uu}


    If you @{"choose" LINK "Setup"} to have the On/Offline gadget
    you will get one button for each interface.
    Pressing the button will put the interface On/Offline.

    The list has also a ContextMenu that may be opened via
    the right mouse button. The menu may be used to put
    an interface On/Offline.

@EndNode

@Node "CGroup" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - Miami ctrls group"

  @{u}@{b}Miami ctrls group@{ub}@{uu}


    If you @{"choose" Link "Setup"} to have the Miami ctrls, you
    get a group made of 3 buttons. They may
    be used to control Miami:

    - Show
      Open Miami GUI

    - Hide
      Iconify Miami GUI

    - Quit
      Quit Miami

@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "MUI_BW.MiamiPanel - Bugs"

  @{u}@{b}Bugs@{ub}@{uu}


    1. No "Suspending" and "Suspended" interfaces states:
       this is a MiamiDx bug.

@EndNode

